    <note type="biography">
        <p>Mathematician and educator. Professor of mathematics at the Royal Military College, Addiscombe, Surrey, 1841–61. Headmaster, Clapham Grammar School, from 1862; later added a department for pupils preparing for admission to military colleges and the Indian Civil Service; the school closed in 1882. Worked as an examiner until 1893.</p></note>
